  "text": "We then used gel shift assays to determine whether OsDr1 and OsDrAp1 interact with DNA. Using the DNA fragment of the rice pal gene from the Ϫ 61 to ϩ 79 region (transcription start site as ϩ 1) as a probe [CITATION_1] and purified recombinant OsDr1 and OsDrAp1 (data not shown), we found that OsDr1 alone had no DNA affinity. There was no detectable shifted band when 250 ng of purified OsDr1 was used in the reactions ( Figure 3C , lane 2). Purified recombinant OsDrAp1 interacted with the DNA and formed three shifted bands, A, B, and C ( Figure 3C , lane 3). One hundred nanograms of OsDrAp1 was enough to detect the DNA-protein interaction in the assays. OsDr1 and OsDrAp1 together produced stronger signals for the three shifted bands and also produced another shifted band ( Figure 3C , lane 4, band D).",
